Load a mark-recapture data set

clean_data.Rd

This function loads and parses a mark recapture data set. It assumes that three files are available, specifying capture, translocation, and survey data.

clean_data(captures, translocations, surveys)

Arguments

captures

Character string path to a capture-recapture detection data csv file.
translocations

Character string path to translocation data csv file.
surveys

Character string path to survey data csv file.

Value

A list containing the data frames resulting from the capture, translocation, and survey data, along with a list of data formatted for use in a mark recapture model (with name "stan_d").

Examples

captures <- system.file("extdata", "capture-example.csv", package = "mrmr")
translocations <- system.file("extdata", "translocation-example.csv",

surveys <- system.file("extdata", "survey-example.csv", package = "mrmr")
